The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Oct. 4: The infrastructure sector has slowed down to register a growth of 5.5 per cent during August, down from 5.8 per cent a year ago. The six-sector infrastructure index had recorded a 9.1 per cent growth in July this year raising the hopes of a major improvement this fiscal in tandem with 8.9 per cent economic growth recorded in the first quarter of 2006-07.

 Mumbai, Oct. 4: The Reserve Bank (RBI) held a meeting with chiefs of 10 select leading banks to discuss monetary and credit issues. The resource management meet, held usually ahead of the credit policy, provides inputs on formulating the RBIs monetary stance. 

 Frankfurt, Oct. 4: Volkswagen has bought a 15.06 per cent stake in German industrial group MAN to create a three-way alliance in the trucking business between MAN and Swedish group Scania. The company has no intention of fully acquiring MAN.

 New Delhi, Oct. 4: The promotional package for small scale industries (SSIs) is likely to cost the government around Rs 2,300 crore and it is expected to be cleared by the cabinet next week.

 New Delhi, Oct. 4: The government has given telecom companies with foreign direct investments (FDIs) three more months to comply with the conditions that were imposed when the cap on foreign equity was increased to 74 per cent.




